    .lead{color:#C8B99A;font-size:1rem;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:2rem}
    .card{background:#1A1208;border:1px solid #3A3020;border-radius:8px;padding:2rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem}
    .card h2{color:#D4A853;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;letter-spacing:.05em}
    .card p{color:#C8B99A;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:.8rem}
    .card ul{list-style:none;padding:0}.card ul li{color:#C8B99A;font-size:.85rem;padding:.3rem 0 .3rem 1.2rem;position:relative}.card ul li::before{content:"·";position:absolute;left:0;color:#D4A853}
    .faq-item{border-bottom:1px solid #3A3020;padding:1rem 0}.faq-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .faq-q{color:#F5E6C8;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:.4rem}
    .faq-a{color:#A89070;font-size:.83rem;line-height:1.7}
    .cta{text-align:center;padding:2rem}.cta h2{color:#D4A853;margin-bottom:1rem}
    .btn-primary{display:inline-block;background:#D4A853;color:#1A1208;padding:.75rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;font-weight:700;margin:.5rem}
    .btn-secondary{display:inline-block;border:1px solid #D4A853;color:#D4A853;padding:.75rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;margin:.5rem}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="lang-bar"><a href="/family-law/domestic-contracts">中文</a><a href="/en/family-law/domestic-contracts" class="active">EN</a></div>
  <Header />
  <div class="page">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/en/">Home</a> › Family Law › Domestic Contracts</div>
    <h1>Domestic Contracts</h1>
    <p class="lead">A domestic contract drafted by a litigator is built to hold up — not just to sign. We draft agreements that protect your interests if things go wrong, because we know exactly how they get challenged in court.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>TYPES OF DOMESTIC CONTRACTS</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Marriage Contract (Prenuptial Agreement) — before or during marriage</li>
        <li>Separation Agreement — on breakdown of marriage or common-law relationship</li>
        <li>Cohabitation Agreement — for common-law couples</li>
        <li>Independent Legal Advice (ILA) Certificate</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>VERIFIED OUTCOME</h2>
      <p>A client's separation agreement was challenged by the other party after signing. We successfully defended the agreement's validity and protected $500,000+ in assets.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is a prenuptial agreement enforceable in Ontario?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes, if properly drafted. A marriage contract must be in writing, signed by both parties, and witnessed. Both parties should have independent legal advice. Courts can set aside agreements that were signed under duress, without disclosure, or without proper legal advice.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is Independent Legal Advice (ILA)?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">ILA means each party has their own lawyer review the agreement independently and explain its consequences. Without ILA, a domestic contract is at greater risk of being set aside by a court later.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can a separation agreement deal with child custody and support?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes, but courts retain jurisdiction to vary child-related terms if circumstances change and the variation is in the best interests of the child. Property and spousal support terms are more binding once properly executed.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card cta">
      <h2>Book a Consultation</h2>
      <a href="tel:6479306688" class="btn-primary">📞 647-930-6688</a>
      <a href="mailto:miao@miaohelaw.ca" class="btn-secondary">Email Us</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>
